divs: Sighting DetailsI went out skywatching taking my night-vision binoculars and digital camera which I've done only 6-7 times lately. I sat watching maybe 30 minutes after seeing a couple falling stars and a plane when I spotted a brighter object out of the NW headed somewhat towards me going SE. I first looked at it through my night-vision binoculars, but I didn't notice strobe lights. I then got my video recorder ready and started filming. I could not see anything in the lcd lens so I just pointed in the direction it was and hoped I was catching this just in case. The object made no sound whatsoever. The object was almost past me when it did some pulsating or something and disappeared, but I want to call it "flickering out." The object stayed in a straight line with plane-like speed. I did manage to catch some video but the quality isn't great cause it's shaky and I played the video to my TV and recorded that with my Iphone so it's a video of a video. I did upload the video to youtube.com from my Iphone and if you search (possible ufo near victoria,tx) or search my username (JoshTX1) you should find it. I do have the original video that I need to upload to the computer but I have to upgrade and pay for nerophoto if that's what it's called. This is a correction from the last almost identical report. In the last report I typed that someone else saw a similar object on the same night as me but it turns out it was 6-26-09 not 7-26-09 and 11:50pm. After this I am going to look up reports again but with the right date...
Summary: Bright object near Victoria, TX. Video on youtube. Correction of original report
